Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.96,0:24:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}不许动\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}Don't move!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.36,0:24:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}手放在背后\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}Hands behind your back!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.76,0:24:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}我什么都不知道\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}I don't know, I don't know, I don't know!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.88,0:24:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}这是什么\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.60,0:24:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}我不知道\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}I don't know!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.56,0:24:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,为了保护阮庄的安全\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}For her own safety,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.40,0:24:48.12,Default,,0,0,0,,她必须继续装作犯罪分子\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}she has to keep her cover story and behave as a criminal...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.12,0:24:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,因此她也必须被逮捕\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}..which means she must also be arrested.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.28,0:25:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}闭嘴\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.52,0:25:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}闭嘴\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.04,0:25:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,象牙全球供应链的一个节点\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}A link in the global supply chain...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.64,0:25:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,被切断了\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}..broken.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.12,0:25:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,阮庄被迅速带走\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}Trang is whisked away,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.44,0:25:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,而卖家则被送到警察局\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}whilst the traders are taken to the police station,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.88,0:25:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,对她的卧底身份毫不知情\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}none the wiser about her involvement.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.68,0:25:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,在接下来的一年 EAGLE在打击全球野生动物贸易的斗争中\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}Over the next year, EAGLE catch 140 more traffickers
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.12,0:25:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,抓获了140多名非法交易人员\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}in the fight against the global wildlife trade.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.52,0:25:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,但对于阮庄来说 这是她的最后一次行动\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}But for Trang, this is her last operation.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.28,0:25:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,因此我们能够拍摄她的面孔\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}It's why we can show her face.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.76,0:25:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}我从事卧底工作\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}I have been doing undercover work
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.36,0:26:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}参与诱捕行动有一段时间了\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}and sting operations for quite a while
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.44,0:26:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}压力确实很大\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}and it can be really stressful.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.72,0:26:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,她不能再逗留在这里了\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}It's not safe for her to stay a minute longer than necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.64,0:26:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,阮庄的最后一项任务 就是从阿比让\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}Trang's final task is to vanish from Abidjan...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.32,0:26:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,彻底消失\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}..for ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.08,0:26:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,世界各地 野生动物的数量正以惊人的速度减少\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}Across the world, the numbers of wild animals are falling alarmingly.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.48,0:26:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,短短二十年里\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}In just two decades -
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.80,0:26:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,也就是自从第一部《地球脉动》\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}since we started making the first Planet Earth series -
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.96,0:26:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,全球野生动物的数量\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}the abundance of wildlife around the globe has dropped,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.64,0:26:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,平均下降了超过30%\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}on average, by over 30%.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.08,0:26:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,我们正面临一场灾难 一场浩劫\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}We're facing a disaster, a catastrophe.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.60,0:26:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,科学家认为 我们正处在物种大灭绝的边缘\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}Scientists say that we're on the edge of a mass extinction.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.80,0:27:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,而这正是人类活动造成的\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}It's being caused by human activity.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.48,0:27:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,因此 人类也有能力阻止这一切\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}So humans also have the power to stop it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.64,0:27:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,拯救物种的艰巨任务 需要很多品质\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}It takes many qualities to save even one species.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.88,0:27:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,决心\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}Determination...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.16,0:27:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,勇气\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}..courage...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.48,0:27:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,以及热情\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}..and passion.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.48,0:27:32.20,Default,,0,0,0,,同时 往往还需要一种品质\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}And often, there's another ingredient that's needed...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.92,0:27:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,放眼未来 敢于创新\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}..the ability to think big.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.68,0:27:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,在维也纳 凯瑟琳娜 · 赫切勒开始了一份新工作\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}In Vienna, Katharina Huchler is just starting a new job.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.40,0:27:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,工资很低\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}The pay is terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.56,0:27:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,工作时间很长\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}The hours are long.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.64,0:27:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,而且没有休息日\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}And there are no days off.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.48,0:28:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,她将成为一名寄养母亲\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}She is about to become a foster mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.52,0:28:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}嗨\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}Hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.36,0:28:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}早上好\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.56,0:28:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}嗨\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}Hi. Hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.64,0:28:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,这些是她的新宝宝\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}And these are her new babies...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.20,0:28:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}你好有精神 嗨\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}You're pretty awake. Hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.08,0:28:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,28只世界上最稀有的鸟类之一\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}..28 of one of the world's rarest birds.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.56,0:28:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}嘿 你好\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}Hey. Hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.12,0:28:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,隐鹮\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}The northern bald ibis.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.04,0:28:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}你会很快爱上它们的\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}You really quickly fall in love with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.00,0:28:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,400多年前在欧洲 隐鹮被猎杀殆尽\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}They were hunted to extinction in Europe over 400 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.32,0:28:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,这些雏鸟是在动物园出生的\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}These chicks were born in a zoo.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.68,0:28:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,凯瑟琳娜的任务 是教它们\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}Katharina's task is to teach them
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.44,0:28:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,如何在野外生存 自由飞翔\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}to become wild, free birds.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.40,0:28:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}来吧来吧\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}Yes, yes, yes. Komm. Komm.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.48,0:28:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,为此 她必须让雏鸟相信 自己是它们的母亲\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}To do that, she must convince them that she is their mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.24,0:28:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,这是一个叫做印随的过程\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}It's a process called imprinting.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.12,0:28:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,这期间 不能让雏鸟看到或听到\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}While it's happening, the chicks must never see or hear
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.96,0:28:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,除了海伦娜的任何人或者声音\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}any other human except Helena,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.52,0:29:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,海伦娜是第二次成为隐鹮的寄养母亲\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}who's an ibis foster mum for the second time.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.00,0:29:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,她们必须穿着完全相同的黄色服装\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}They must always wear identical yellow clothes
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.92,0:29:10.20,Default,,0,0,0,,并且不停发出相同的声音\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}and repeat the same noises again and again.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.40,0:29:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}我们模仿成年隐鹮的声音 像是\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}We mimic the sounds the adults make, it's like...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.28,0:29:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}我的模仿还不够好\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}But I'm not good yet at doing it!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.00,0:29:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}晚安\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}Goodnight.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.56,0:29:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,她们陪着雏鸟直到睡着\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}They're here when the chicks fall asleep...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.72,0:29:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}做个好梦\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}Sleep well.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.92,0:29:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,雏鸟醒来一睁眼看到的也是她们\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}..and the first thing they see when they awake.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.00,0:29:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}早上好\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}Good morning, waldies! Hallo!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.16,0:29:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}去吃点早饭吧 好不好\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}Let's have something to eat, shall we? Yes, let's eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.12,0:29:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}它们有点像人类宝宝\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}They're a bit like every human baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.68,0:29:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}它们需要一天从早到晚\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}They just need their food bit by bit by bit
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.40,0:29:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}一口一口吃饭\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}all day long.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.76,0:29:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}很好很好\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}Yes, yes, yes, yes, yes, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.68,0:29:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}糟了 出错了\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}Oh, no, we did it all wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.28,0:29:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}就跟给宝宝换尿布一样\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}It's really like changing the nappies of the babies.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.84,0:30:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,负责28只雏鸟的吃喝拉撒\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}28 mouths to feed and bottoms to wipe,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.56,0:30:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,还要不断跟雏鸟交流\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}and all the time talking to the birds.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.60,0:30:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}来吧来吧\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}Komm, komm, waldies! Komm, komm!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.96,0:30:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}感觉很累\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}Feeling really tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.60,0:30:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}想多睡一会儿\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}Yeah, I'd really like to sleep a little bit more.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.92,0:30:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,随着时间的流逝 他们的感情越来越深\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}As the weeks pass, the bond grows.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.64,0:30:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,接下来 雏鸟要进入\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}And then it is time for their next stage
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.56,0:30:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,成为野生隐鹮的新阶段\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}in becoming wild birds.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.00,0:30:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,他们来到奥地利阿尔卑斯山的一片草地上\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}They move to a field in the Austrian Alps.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.84,0:30:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,雏鸟已经长出了可以飞行的羽毛\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}They've now grown their adult flight feathers...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.68,0:30:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,但它们内心还只是雏鸟\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}...but they're still chicks on the inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.72,0:30:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,因此 印随工作还要继续\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}So the imprinting must continue.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.60,0:30:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}我们用这个手势\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}With this hand gesture we do,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.08,0:30:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}模仿成年隐鹮的喙\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}we imitate the bill of an adult ibis
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.12,0:30:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}并配合隐鹮的叫声\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}and we combine it with the greeting sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.08,0:30:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}像这样\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}So, this is...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.28,0:31:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,这样的模仿是出于一个重要的原因\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}All this imprinting is for a very important reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.72,0:31:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,隐鹮是候鸟\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}These are migratory birds.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.44,0:31:09.08,Default,,0,0,0,,秋季 它们必须飞往南方\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}In autumn, they must fly south
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.08,0:31:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,飞往位于意大利的温暖觅食地\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}to their warm feeding grounds in Italy.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.32,0:31:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,而这是个问题\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}And that is a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.08,0:31:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}它们知道自己必须去往某个地方\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}They know that they need to go somewhere,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.56,0:31:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}但不知道往哪个方向飞 要飞多远\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}but they don't know in which direction and how far.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.08,0:31:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}它们需要从父母那里学习迁徙路线\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}So they need to learn the route from their parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.80,0:31:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,现在这成了寄养母亲的工作\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}Their human mothers must show them the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.32,0:31:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,而这需要一点创意\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}And that requires a little ingenuity.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.72,0:31:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,是时候检验印随的效果了\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}This is where the imprinting is put to the test.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.16,0:32:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,如果她们坐在一架飞机上\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}Will the birds follow them...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.88,0:32:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,隐鹮会跟着她们吗\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}..even in a microlight?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.84,0:32:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}来吧来吧\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}Komm, komm!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.64,0:32:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}来吧来吧鸟儿们\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}Komm, komm, waldies!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.60,0:32:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}来吧来吧\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}Komm, komm!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.12,0:32:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}来吧来吧鸟儿们\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}Come come, ibis! Come, come!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.00,0:32:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,过近的距离对于隐鹮和人都很危险\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}Getting too close is dangerous for both birds and humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.44,0:32:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}有只鸟飞在绳索间\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}There's a bird in the lines!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.72,0:32:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}其他都飞在前面\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}The others are all at the front.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.04,0:32:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}有只鸟飞得太近了\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}There's one near the lines.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.08,0:32:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}靠近左侧的绳索\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}Close to the lines on the left.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.76,0:32:45.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}没问题了\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}It's all fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.04,0:32:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,尽管开头不太顺利\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}After a wobbly start...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.72,0:33:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,但最终隐鹮老实了下来\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}..at last they settle.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.52,0:33:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}出发\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.52,0:33:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,印随工作大成功\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}The imprinting has worked.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.52,0:33:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}隐鹮今天表现非常好\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}Our birds did very well today.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.16,0:33:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,但最大的挑战还在后面\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}But their biggest challenge is still to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.96,0:33:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,齐勒塔尔阿尔卑斯山脉\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}The Zillertal Alps.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.12,0:33:49.16,Default,,0,0,0,,岩石和冰雪组成巨大的一堵墙\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}A great wall of rock and ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.16,0:34:00.60,Default,,0,0,0,,这将是隐鹮生命中\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}It's going to be the most important flight
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.60,0:34:02.52,Default,,0,0,0,,最重要的一次飞行\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}of their young lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.64,0:34:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,这将会让它们精疲力竭\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}It will take them to the very edge of exhaustion.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.84,0:34:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}很多年轻的鸟在第一次迁徙时 失去了性命\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}A lot of young birds die during their first migration.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.48,0:34:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}它们过于缺乏经验\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}They are still so inexperienced.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.44,0:34:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,这对于寄养母亲和飞行员来说同样危险\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}There's also danger for the foster mothers and the pilots.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.00,0:34:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,如果飞机出了问题\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}If there is a problem with the microlights,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.28,0:34:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,根本没有安全的地方着陆\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}there is no safe place to land.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.60,0:34:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,要想飞越这些山峰\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}To gain enough height to fly over these mountains...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.52,0:34:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,它们必须找到叫做热气流的上升气流\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}..they must find columns of rising air called thermals.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.52,0:34:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,这种技术往往需要鸟儿\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}A skill these birds would normally learn
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.72,0:34:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,在跟随父母迁徙时习得\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}by following their natural mothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.84,0:35:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,找到上升气流 需要精湛的飞行技术\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}It takes expert piloting to find the thermals.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.16,0:35:20.52,Default,,0,0,0,,而上升气流中\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}Once within one,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.52,0:35:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,气流猛烈 难以控制\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}it's turbulent and unpredictable.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.20,0:35:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}高度很高了\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}We're very high now.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.88,0:35:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,每次转弯 她们都要确认\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}With every turn, the mothers must make sure
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.28,0:35:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,28只隐鹮是否都跟上了\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}all 28 birds are following.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.12,0:36:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}有一只脱离大部队了\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}One's separate from the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.48,0:36:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}28只隐鹮都在\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}All 28 birds here.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.60,0:36:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,最终 它们飞过了最高的山峰\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}At last, they make it over the highest ridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.44,0:36:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,从此以后 飞行就轻松多了\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}From now on, it should be easy flying.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.88,0:37:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}我们的目的 不仅是拯救隐鹮\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}What we are trying to do, apart from saving the ibis,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.08,0:37:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}还是给人们带来希望\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}is trying to give hope to people.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.12,0:37:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}如果你可以让一个物种重获新生\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}If you can bring back one species,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.20,0:37:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}其他物种自然同样可以\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}you can also do it with others.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.20,0:37:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,曾经濒临灭绝的物种 如今再度振翅高飞\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}A species once left for dead now has a future.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.56,0:37:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,它们飞向自然保护区\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}And they head for their safe winter home
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.16,0:37:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,那里将成为它们安全的冬季家园\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}in a protected nature reserve.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.72,0:38:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,但正如在这个系列中看到的\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}But as we have seen throughout this series,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.76,0:38:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,许多物种正在失去它们赖以生存的野生栖息地\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}many species are losing the wild habitats they need to survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.80,0:38:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,而这正是导致灭绝的最大原因\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}It's the biggest cause of extinction.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.36,0:38:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,这一点在亚马逊雨林中最为明显\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}Nowhere is this more apparent than in the Amazon rainforest.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.36,0:38:56.12,Default,,0,0,0,,二十年里 《地球脉动》摄制组\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}Our Planet Earth crews have filmed here many times
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.12,0:38:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,多次在这里拍摄\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}over the last two decades.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.92,0:39:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,而这段时间里 超过160亿颗树\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}And in that time, over 16,000 million trees...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.68,0:39:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,遭到砍伐\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}..have been felled.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.44,0:39:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,为了保护生活在此的无数物种\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}To safeguard the countless species that live here...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.84,0:39:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,雨林本身必须得到保护\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}..the forest itself must be protected..
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.88,0:39:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,而有一股力量 正为此而崛起\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}And there's a force rising up to do just that.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.12,0:39:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}瞧这只蚂蚁 贝拉\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}Look at this ant, Bella
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.04,0:39:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}孤零零一只蚂蚁\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}This ant is all alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.72,0:39:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}脆弱无助\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}It's helpless.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.48,0:39:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}但蚂蚁群团结一心\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}But when they are all together
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.88,0:39:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}便攻无不克\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}they are strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.48,0:40:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,亚历珊德拉 · 科拉普是蒙杜鲁库族的领袖之一\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}Alessandra Korap is one of the leaders of the Munduruku.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.00,0:40:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,他们是这部分亚马逊的守护者\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}They have been the guardians of this part of the Amazon
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.48,0:40:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,有着数千年的历史\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}for thousands of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.32,0:40:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}我们蒙杜鲁库族人\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}We, the Munduruku
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.24,0:40:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}是这片森林的一部分\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}we are part of this forest
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.16,0:40:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}我们必须像蚂蚁一样团结一心\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}and we must keep being like this little ant.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.60,0:40:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}对抗破坏森林的人\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}We have to keep bothering people.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.96,0:40:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}我爱这片森林\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}I love this forest!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.44,0:40:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}既是市场 又是药房\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}It's a market, it's a pharmacy.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.08,0:40:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}但这片森林不仅仅只属于蒙杜鲁库族\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}But the forest is not just there for the Munduruku.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.12,0:40:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}而是属于整个地球\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}It's there for the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.44,0:40:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,亚历珊德拉小时候 这片亚马逊森林\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}When she was a child, this part of the Amazon forest
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.32,0:41:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,是一望无际的处女地\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}stretched unbroken for hundreds of miles.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.84,0:41:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,但如今它被割成碎片\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}Now it's being carved up...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.56,0:41:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,为了矿产与木材\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}..for mining, for timber,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.64,0:41:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,而最主要的是为了农业\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}but most of all for agriculture.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.96,0:41:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,这里是亚马逊保卫战的前线\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}This is the front line in the battle for the Amazon,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.40,0:41:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,这场战争沾满了血泪\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}and it is a deadly one.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.96,0:41:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,过去的十年里 巴西有超过300人\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}In the last decade, more than 300 people have been murdered
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.48,0:41:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,为保护环境而死\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}in Brazil defending the environment.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.48,0:41:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}保护森林时\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}When you protect a forest
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.36,0:41:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}总是会面临生命危险\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}our lives are at stake.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.68,0:41:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}我随时可能失去生命\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}I could be killed at any moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.72,0:41:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}他们两次试图杀死我\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}They tried to kill me twice
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.24,0:42:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}试图杀害其他部落领袖\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}They tried to kill other leaders
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.96,0:42:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}被关在屋子里 活活烧死\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}by burning them alive, inside their house.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.36,0:42:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,像许多原住民群体一样\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}The Munduruku, like many indigenous groups,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.88,0:42:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,蒙杜鲁库族与世隔绝\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}live in isolated communities
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.48,0:42:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,经常遭到开采 农业和伐木等活动的侵扰\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}vulnerable to attack from miners, farmers and loggers.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.96,0:42:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}伐木工人来到这里\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}The loggers are coming in.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.04,0:42:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}总是拿着枪走来走去\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}They always go around with their gunmen.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.56,0:42:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}很多部落里的人\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}A lot of people don't know what's happening
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.48,0:42:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}不知道发生了什么\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}here in the territory.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.96,0:42:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}因此他们以为这是我们编造出来的谎言\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}So they think it's a lie, that we're making it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.04,0:42:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}为什么要砍这么多树呢\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}Why do they have to cut down so much?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.92,0:42:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,亚马逊的未来 是由远在3200公里外的巴西政府决定的\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}The Amazon's future is decided 2,000 miles away.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.72,0:42:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,在这里 议员正在讨论\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}Here, in the parliament of Brazil,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.52,0:42:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,制定新的法案 允许对原住民土地\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}new laws are being debated to allow the exploitation
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.36,0:43:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,进行商业开发\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}of their traditional tribal land.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.68,0:43:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,但亚历珊德拉不甘于此\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}But Alessandra has a plan -
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.28,0:43:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,她计划联合其他部落\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}to unite with other tribes
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.12,0:43:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,发起一场规模空前的抗议\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}and organise a protest so big
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.96,0:43:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,让政府听到他们的声音\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}that it cannot be ignored.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.12,0:43:24.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}我们需要做好准备\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}We need to prepare ourselves
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.32,0:43:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}前往城市\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}to go to the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.72,0:43:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}当我们离开家园\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}When we leave our home
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.40,0:43:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}前往首都巴西利亚时\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}to go to Brasilia
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.00,0:43:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}我们发现了许多敌人\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}we find many enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.72,0:43:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}西装革履的人\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}And the ones who wear suits
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.44,0:43:52.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}正在制造战争 制定法律\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}are making war, making laws.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.44,0:43:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}我们曾经用弓箭\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}Before we used to use arrows
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.28,0:44:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}保卫我们的领地\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}to fight for our territory.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.00,0:44:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}如今一切都不一样了\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}Today is different.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.60,0:44:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,这趟前往首都的旅程 将花费三天\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}It's a three-day journey to the capital city.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.44,0:44:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,曾经雨林覆盖的土地\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}Trucks rumble to and from the fields...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.48,0:44:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,如今变成了农田\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}..land that used to be rainforest.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.32,0:44:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,隆隆的卡车装满了大豆\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}They're carrying thousands of tonnes of soya beans.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.00,0:44:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,从亚马逊深处运往世界各地\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}It's shipped from the heart of the Amazon across the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.04,0:44:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,这些大豆不是用来养活人类\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}Not to feed humans...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.72,0:44:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,而是用来喂养家畜\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}..but to feed livestock.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.16,0:44:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}我们的森林\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}Our forest,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.24,0:44:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}我们的亚马逊\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}our Amazon,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.52,0:44:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}遭到严重破坏\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}is being destroyed
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.28,0:44:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}就只是为了养鸡 养猪\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}for you to have your chicken farm, your pig farm.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.48,0:45:09.56,Default,,0,0,0,,最终 亚历珊德拉抵达了巴西利亚\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}Eventually, Alessandra makes it to Brasilia.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.04,0:45:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,她的抗议行动引起了全国的关注\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}News of the protest has spread all over the country.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.48,0:45:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,有200个不同的部落加入了她的行列\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}200 groups have united in a huge camp.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.88,0:45:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,有来自巴西东北部的苏库鲁人\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}From the northeast of Brazil - the Xukuru.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.88,0:45:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,有来自亚马逊南部的卡拉加人\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}From the southern edge of the Amazon - the Karaja.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.68,0:45:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}如果我们同意这项法案\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}If we decide now to agree to the approval of this law
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.32,0:45:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}就等于将我们的子孙后代置之死地\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}then we are agreeing to the deaths of our children.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.64,0:45:50.28,Default,,0,0,0,,抗议活动持续了十天\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}For ten days, they protest against the proposed laws.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.40,0:45:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}我觉得我们就像小蚂蚁 与国家机器斗争\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}I see us as little ants, fighting against the machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.40,0:46:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}但当我们团结起来\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}But when we get together
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.92,0:46:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}他们就不得不重视\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}then we start to bother them.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.04,0:46:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}就会听见我们的声音 感受到我们的力量\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}Then they feel it, then they hear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.56,0:46:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,亚历珊德拉和其他部落领袖\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}Alessandra and the other leaders have created
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.16,0:46:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,掀起了巴西历史上 最大的原住民抗议活动\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}the biggest protest by indigenous people ever held in Brazil.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.40,0:46:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,最终努力没有白费 其中一项法案被推翻了\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}Later, one of the proposed laws was withdrawn.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.20,0:46:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,这是亚历珊德拉为保护巴西自然资源\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}A small but significant victory
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.96,0:46:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,取得的一个虽小 却意义重大的胜利\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}in Alessandra's fight for Brazil's wild places.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.04,0:46:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,目前 野生动物面临的最大危机\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}The destruction of habitats is currently the biggest threat
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.36,0:46:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,是栖息地的丧失\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}to the survival of animal species.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.32,0:47:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,然而 更大的危机正在逼近\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}But there is an even greater disaster on the horizon.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.80,0:47:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,那就是气候变化\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}Our climate is changing.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.44,0:47:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,季节变得越来越不稳定且极端\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}Seasons have become unpredictable and more extreme.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.40,0:47:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,地球正在变暖\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}Our planet is getting hotter.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.36,0:47:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,科学家预测 如果全球气温上升\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}Scientists predict that if the global temperature
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.04,0:47:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,超过2摄氏度\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}rises by over two degrees,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.80,0:47:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,那么气候变化就可能成为 导致物种灭绝的最主要原因\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}it is likely to become the number one cause of extinction.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.28,0:47:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,要阻止气候变化\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}To halt climate change,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.08,0:47:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,也许需要政客们自身也成为英雄\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}perhaps politicians need to become heroes, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.60,0:47:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}大家晚上好 欢迎来到格拉斯哥\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}Hello, good evening, and a warm welcome to Glasgow
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.20,0:47:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}参加这场期待已久的气候峰会 COP26的开幕\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}and the start of the long-awaited climate summit, COP26.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.40,0:47:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}各国领导人 杰出的科学家\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}World leaders, prominent scientists
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.92,0:47:47.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}都已做好准备\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}and advisers all ready for 12 days of...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.24,0:47:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,默罕默德 · 纳希德是一名政治家\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}Mohamed Nasheed is a politician,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.88,0:47:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,曾担任马尔代夫的总统\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}the former president of the Maldives.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.00,0:47:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}医生说 他们从我身上\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}The doctors said that they took 16 ball bearings
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.76,0:48:00.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}取出了16颗钢珠\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}from all parts of my body.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.68,0:48:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}我昏迷了两天\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}I was unconscious for two days.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.40,0:48:10.44,Default,,0,0,0,,他的政治生涯充满艰辛 经受过酷刑 牢狱之灾\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}Over his political career, he has been tortured, imprisoned
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.44,0:48:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,并且刚刚在刺杀下逃过一劫\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}and recently survived an assassination attempt.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.72,0:48:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,但这期间\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}But during that time,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.44,0:48:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,他也一直在为应对气候变化而奋斗\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}he's also fought relentlessly against climate change.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.32,0:48:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}很荣幸邀请默罕默德 · 纳希德\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}..pleasure to be able to bring you Mohamed Nasheed.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.56,0:48:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,在格拉斯哥气候峰会COP26的前一天\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}In Glasgow, on the eve of climate conference COP26,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.04,0:48:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,他在一个集会上发表了演讲\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}he is addressing a rally.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.92,0:48:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}谢谢\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.52,0:48:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}非常感谢\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.60,0:48:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}我们来到COP26\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}So, we come to COP26
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.40,0:48:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}是为了探索人类的未来\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}to find out whether we still have a future.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.84,0:48:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}如果我们不能签署一个有法律效力的协议\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}If we cannot have a legally binding agreement
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.36,0:48:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}阻止全球气温升高\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}not to push global temperatures
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.36,0:49:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}超过1.5度\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}above 1.5 degrees,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.88,0:49:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}我的祖国就将彻底消失\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}my country will be gone,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.44,0:49:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}世界上所有珊瑚礁和大部分雨林\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}as will all the world's coral reefs
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.04,0:49:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}也会随之消亡\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}and most of the rainforests.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.68,0:49:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}仅仅为了能在短短几年内\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}Is all this devastation really worth it,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.00,0:49:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}继续燃烧煤炭以及化石燃料\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}so that we can continue to burn coal and fossil fuel
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.64,0:49:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}而引发如此灾难 真的值得吗\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}for a few more years?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.52,0:49:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}我一生\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}I have spent a lifetime
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.56,0:49:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}都在为我的国家而战\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}fighting for my country,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.96,0:49:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}而且我现在比以往任何时候都更有决心\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}and with more determination than ever,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.96,0:49:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}因为我清楚 我生活在这颗美丽星球上的时间可能已经不多了\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}because I know my time on Earth might be cut short.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.68,0:49:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,默罕默德 · 纳希德对大自然的热爱\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}Mohamed Nasheed's passion for the natural world
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.96,0:49:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,始于他第一次见到珊瑚礁\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}began the first time he saw a coral reef.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.92,0:50:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}我最早的记忆\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}My earliest memory
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.08,0:50:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}就是与海洋和珊瑚礁在一起\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}is with the ocean and the reef.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.32,0:50:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}我们是第一代真正见到珊瑚礁的人\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}We were the first generation to actually see the reef.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.88,0:50:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}潜水面罩和护目镜在60年代末\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}Masks and goggles came to the Maldives
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.36,0:50:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}70年代初出现在马尔代夫\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}in the late '60s, early '70s.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.80,0:50:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}一旦把珊瑚礁看作一个活着的生物\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}Once we started seeing the reef as a living creature...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.04,0:50:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}我们就会惊叹不已\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}..we were just dumbfounded.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.36,0:50:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,然而纳希德深爱的珊瑚礁\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}But Nasheed's beloved coral is now the habitat
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.12,0:50:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,如今是受气候变化威胁最大的栖息地\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}that is most threatened by climate change.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.28,0:50:49.16,Default,,0,0,0,,温度上升的临界值是1.5度\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}The critical tipping point is a 1.5 degree temperature rise.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.36,0:50:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,一旦高过这个数字 大多数珊瑚礁将死亡\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}Beyond that, most reefs will die,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.44,0:50:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,留下一片废墟\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}leaving nothing but rubble.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.20,0:51:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}当你把目光放的长远\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}When you think of a bigger picture,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.92,0:51:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}自己一个人的生命便不再那么重要了\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}then your own life is not so important.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.40,0:51:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}重要的是能在生命中做些什么\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}It's what you want to get done which is important.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:15.24,0:51:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,纳希德的目标 是说服政治家减少使用\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}Nasheed's aim is to persuade politicians to cut the use
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.36,0:51:21.80,Default,,0,0,0,,煤炭和其他化石燃料\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}of coal and other fossil fuels.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.60,0:51:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,他在每个气候会议上 都重复着这份诉求\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}He repeats this plea at every climate conference.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.28,0:51:29.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}你必须说服人们\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}You need to be able to convince people,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.88,0:51:32.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}引导人们\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}try to educate people.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.04,0:51:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}我们处于危机之中\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}We are in trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.84,0:51:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}如果地球气温升高超过1.5度 人类将无法生存\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}We will not survive if the planet is heated above 1.5 degrees.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.36,0:51:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}我们必须立刻采取行动\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}We must act now.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.56,0:51:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,一开始 有些国家领导人\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}At first, journalists are reporting on some eye-catching promises
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.84,0:51:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,做出了引人注目的承诺\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}made by heads of state.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.00,0:51:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}18个国家承诺\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}18 countries have committed themselves
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.64,0:51:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}制定一个停止使用燃煤发电厂的计划\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}to a plan to stop using coal-fired power plants.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.44,0:51:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}如今这是一个关乎选举的问题\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}It is an election issue now.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:54.28,0:51:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}因此国家领导人才会做出这样的承诺\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}That is why world leaders have joined the rhetoric.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.96,0:52:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,下一阶段 将承诺落实为具体计划\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}The next stage - turning promises into solid plans.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:03.68,0:52:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,纳希德正在幕后努力推动这些计划\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}And Nasheed is busy working behind the scenes.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.12,0:52:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}如果他们不同意 我们就给总统以及部长打电话\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}If they don't agree, we will ring their ministers, their presidents
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.08,0:52:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}在线上谈判\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}and get them online.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.80,0:52:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}这就是我们要做的事情\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}I think that's what we're trying to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.92,0:52:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}立刻行动吧\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}So let's do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.36,0:52:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}你好 总理\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}How are you, Prime Minister?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.92,0:52:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}我听得很清楚\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}Yeah, OK.  I can hear you,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.16,0:52:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}但我听总理的声音更清楚\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}but I can hear the Prime Minister much clearer.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.44,0:52:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,所有国家都要签署最终的协议\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}All countries need to agree to the final text -
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.80,0:52:28.04,Default,,0,0,0,,但有些国家拒绝了\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}and some won't.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.04,0:52:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}坚持使用化石燃料的人\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}People who want to continue fossil fuel,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.48,0:52:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}我认为 是坏人\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}I think, are the bad guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.88,0:52:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}而那些愿意做出改变的人 我则认为是好人\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}And people who want to change, I feel, are the good guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.32,0:52:41.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}谢谢 非常感谢\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}Thank you. Thank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.76,0:52:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,14天后 COP26闭幕\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}After 14 days, this COP closes...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.64,0:52:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,虽然取得了一些进展\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}..with some progress,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.12,0:52:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,但也有许多妥协\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}but also with big compromises.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.32,0:52:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}一份协议中关于煤炭使用的关键部分\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}An agreement was finally reached this evening
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.04,0:52:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}在最后一刻被加以修改 放宽标准\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}after a key section on the future use of coal
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.48,0:52:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}才终于得到通过\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}was at the last moment watered down.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.04,0:53:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,关键的新提案被搁置\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}Without urgent new commitments,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:04.44,0:53:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,1.5度的目标将无法实现\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}the target of 1.5 degrees will be missed.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.92,0:53:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}简直是灾难\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}It is disastrous.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.92,0:53:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}这将\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}It will...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.44,0:53:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}想象一下 如果你能理解这一切\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}If you picture this, if you can fathom it...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.84,0:53:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}珊瑚礁将白化\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}..the coral will bleach
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.76,0:53:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}最终死去\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}and they will die,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.76,0:53:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}而当珊瑚礁死亡\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}and when they are dead,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.92,0:53:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}其中的鱼类以及海洋生命\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}the fish and the marine life that lives there...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.40,0:53:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}也将不复存在\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}..cease to exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.68,0:53:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}你本以为你的总理\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}You would have thought that your normal prime minister
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.96,0:53:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}和总统\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}and president...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.20,0:53:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}能更好的理解这一切的重要性\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}..would have a better grip on understanding things.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.12,0:53:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}而不是一味地坚持\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}And not just go on and on and on
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.24,0:53:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}维护自己的生活方式\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}about protecting their way of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.24,0:54:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}所以看到那些政客如此无知\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}So it's frustrating to see politicians...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.60,0:54:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}真的很让人沮丧\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}..who doesn't seem to understand it.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.56,0:54:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,根据现行的政策\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}With current policies,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.76,0:54:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,99%的珊瑚礁将在30年内\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}99% of coral reefs could be gone...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.84,0:54:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,彻底消失\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}..in under 30 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.44,0:54:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,其他的生态系统也将随之衰败\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}Other habitats will follow.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.40,0:54:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}不能因此失去希望\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}You can't lose hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.40,0:54:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}也不能因此而放弃\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}You cannot give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.68,0:54:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}我不会停下脚步\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}I will not stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.16,0:54:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,纳希德相信存在一个解决方案\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}Nasheed believes there is a solution.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.64,0:54:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}随着环境问题逐渐成为选举的重点\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}The more environment becomes an election issue,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.64,0:54:57.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}会有越来越多领导人采取行动应对气候变化\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}there will be more action on climate.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.64,0:55:03.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}请把你手中每一张选票\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}Every time you vote, in every election,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.08,0:55:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\1c&HFFFF80&}都投给我们美丽的地球\N{\fs12\1c&H00FFFFFF\b0}please tick the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.56,0:55:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,拯救物种的艰巨任务不能只靠\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}The challenge of saving species can't be left to a few
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.52,0:55:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,在逆境中奋斗的少数英雄人物\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}heroic individuals working against the odds.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.00,0:55:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,拥有更大权力的人\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}It's those in positions of great power
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.64,0:55:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,才能做出更大的改变\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}who can make the most difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.24,0:55:38.12,Default,,0,0,0,,因此 最终他们必须担起最大的责任\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}So, ultimately, it is they who must take the most responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.12,0:55:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,也许我们的职责之一 便是向他们问责\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}Perhaps one of our roles is to hold them to account.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.44,0:55:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,对于很多物种来说 时间已所剩无几\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}Time is running out for many species,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.12,0:55:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,但我真心相信 如果现在在这个关键时刻\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}but I truly believe that if the right decisions are made now,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.24,0:55:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,能做出正确的决定\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}at this critical moment,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.68,0:55:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,所有生命仍有一个光明的未来\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}there could still be a bright future for all life
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.20,0:56:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,在我们美丽的地球上生生不息 脉动不止\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}on our wonderful planet Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.00,0:56:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs20\fad(3000,3000)\bord0\pos(192,190)\b0}自本纪录片拍摄以来
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.16,0:56:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs20\fad(3000,3000)\bord0\pos(192,260)\b0}悲情圣地亚哥辞世
Dialogue: 0,0:56:11.64,0:56:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs20\fad(3000,3000)\bord0\pos(192,80)\b0}但它的物种群落日益壮大
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.20,0:56:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs20\fad(3000,3000)\bord0\pos(192,240)\b0}六十只隐鹮振翅 踏上了迁徙的征程
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.00,0:56:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs20\fad(3000,3000)\bord0\pos(192,180)\b0}纳希德坚持在气候峰会上不断提出诉求
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.28,0:56:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs20\fad(3000,3000)\bord0\pos(192,250)\b0}阮庄投身于新一代卧底警探的培养工作
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.36,0:56:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs20\fad(3000,3000)\bord0\pos(192,190)\b0}二十头黑犀被运至安全的家园
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.00,0:57:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs20\fad(3000,3000)\bord0\pos(192,285)\b0}在巴西 六个原住民土地
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.04,0:57:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs20\fad(3000,3000)\bord0\pos(192,285)\b0}如今依法受到保护
Dialogue: 0,0:57:10.04,0:57:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,「栖息地探索者」生动地展现动物和它们的栖息地\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}Habitat Explorer brings animals and their habitats to life.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.96,0:57:17.72,Default,,0,0,0,,探索这个免费互动程序并制作折纸动物\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}Explore this free interactive, and make origami animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.72,0:57:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,前往bbc.co.uk/planetearth3\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}Go to bbc.co.uk/planetearth3
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.72,0:57:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,点击链接进入开放大学\N{\fs12\1c&HFFFF80&\b0}and follow the links to the Open University.
